## Throwing Errors

### Good â€” Standard NestJS Exceptions (Recommended)

```typescript
import { Injectable, NotFoundException, ConflictException } from '@nestjs/common';
import { AuthError, AuthErrorMessage } from '@application/shared/errors';

@Injectable()
export class AuthService {
  async findOne(id: string): Promise<User> {
    const user = await this.userRepository.findOne(id);
    if (!user) {
      throw new NotFoundException({
        code: AuthError.USER_NOT_FOUND,
        message: AuthErrorMessage[AuthError.USER_NOT_FOUND],
      });
    }
    return user;
  }

  async create(dto: CreateUserRequestDto): Promise<User> {
    const existing = await this.userRepository.findByEmail(dto.email);
    if (existing) {
      throw new ConflictException({
        code: AuthError.EMAIL_EXISTS,
        message: AuthErrorMessage[AuthError.EMAIL_EXISTS],
      });
    }
    return this.userRepository.create(dto);
  }
}
```

### Good â€” ProblemDetailsException (Full Control)

```typescript
import { ProblemDetailsException } from '@sjfrhafe/nest-problem-details';
import { AuthError, AuthErrorMessage, ErrorType } from '@application/shared/errors';

throw new ProblemDetailsException({
  type: ErrorType[AuthError.USER_NOT_FOUND],
  title: 'User Not Found',
  status: 404,
  detail: AuthErrorMessage[AuthError.USER_NOT_FOUND],
  code: AuthError.USER_NOT_FOUND,
});
```

### Bad â€” Magic Strings

```typescript
// âťŚ Never do this
throw new NotFoundException('User not found');
throw new NotFoundException('Cannot find user');  // Inconsistent message
throw new Error('Something went wrong');  // Generic, no code
```

## Validation Before Operations

Always validate entity existence before performing operations.

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class ProfileService {
  async update(id: string, dto: UpdateProfileRequestDto): Promise<Profile> {
    const profile = await this.profileRepository.findOne(id);
    if (!profile) {
      throw new NotFoundException({
        code: ProfileError.NOT_FOUND,
        message: ProfileErrorMessage[ProfileError.NOT_FOUND],
      });
    }

    // Validate business rules
    if (profile.status === ProfileStatus.COMPLETED) {
      throw new BadRequestException({
        code: ProfileError.CANNOT_MODIFY_COMPLETED,
        message: ProfileErrorMessage[ProfileError.CANNOT_MODIFY_COMPLETED],
      });
    }

    return this.profileRepository.update(id, dto);
  }

  async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {
    const profile = await this.profileRepository.findOne(id);
    if (!profile) {
      throw new NotFoundException({
        code: ProfileError.NOT_FOUND,
        message: ProfileErrorMessage[ProfileError.NOT_FOUND],
      });
    }
    await this.profileRepository.delete(id);
  }
}
```

## HTTP Status Code Mapping

| Scenario | Exception | Status |
|----------|-----------|--------|
| Entity not found | `NotFoundException` | 404 |
| Duplicate/conflict | `ConflictException` | 409 |
| Invalid input | `BadRequestException` | 400 |
| Validation failure | Auto via pipe | 400 |
| Not authenticated | `UnauthorizedException` | 401 |
| Not authorized | `ForbiddenException` | 403 |
| Server error | `InternalServerErrorException` | 500 |

## Security (RFC 9457)

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|------------|
| Stack trace exposure | `includeStackTrace: false` in production |
| Internal path leak | Use generic `instance` or omit |
| Implementation details | `detail` must be user-friendly, not technical |
| Sensitive data in errors | Never include passwords, tokens, internal IDs |

## Best Practices

- Use RFC 9457 Problem Details for ALL errors
- Centralize error codes in enum + message map files
- Always include `code` field for machine-readable errors
- Standard NestJS exceptions auto-convert via global filter
- Validate entity existence before update/delete operations
- Never expose stack traces in production
- Group errors by feature - `user.errors.ts`, `order.errors.ts`
- Use `ErrorType` for consistent type URIs
- **Never use magic strings** - all error codes/messages in centralized files
- **Include error codes** - machine-readable codes for client handling
- **Use appropriate HTTP status codes** - 404 for not found, 409 for conflict, etc.
- Log appropriately - error level for 5xx, warn level for 4xx
- Structure error responses consistently - same format for all endpoints


## Common Mistakes

- Magic strings instead of error enums
- Different messages for the same error
- Inconsistent error response formats
- Missing error codes (only returning messages)
- Exposing stack traces in production
- Not validating entity existence before operations
- Throwing generic `Error` instead of NestJS exceptions
- Forgetting to include `code` in exception response
- Not enabling `ProblemDetailsFilter` globally
- Catching errors without proper handling or re-throwing
